caption: Luckily the quality and freshness of their food hasn't been led astray by the pandemic. The yellow is curry is absolutely a MUST have! I had their chicken Masaman was  really good and was delivered by GRUBHUB and it was actually surprisingly hot and good. Kudos  to great packaging and grubhub this time as  it was delivered on time as expected👍 my only issue is that I wish i had a little more rice, otherwise a great meal that was 🔥 and flavorful. My vegetarian son loves their veggie options and has great vegan options too. Try them today for a hot good meal with grub hub delivery or walk up now. UPDATE- They've now got a great walk up for take out, just use the street parking in front(2 spots!) walk up and ring white door bell, pay  and in minutes you're on you're on your way back home. Their Walk up gives you a similar experience as the former pick up inside, fast and easy . with the walk up today i got chicken Pad Kee Mao that was good and filled me up.

This is definitely one of the best place to eat in the region. Always when I come there I am absolutely happy. They always keep their very high  standard service and the topmost level of meals  they serve. You can never go wrong with this place. Highly  recommended.

This is a perfect downtown restaurant. This has a different feeling and the food is so authentic. Prices are good and you won’t go wrong with almost any meal. The service is also good and food is always ready pretty fast, even with a large group. One of the few restaurants in Elgin that I recommend to friends.
Best thai food I have ever had. If you want something with a kick, try the drunken noodles with chicken. Great service, fresh veggies, delicious!
Had a pretty good take out. I ordered red curry and pad woosen. Pad woosen was good, buy red curry was awesome! The owner seemed friendly.
The food is great!

I love to order take out from Toom Toom Thai. The spring rolls and pad thai are always delicious. I also love their mango and sticky rice dessert. Yum!

I've ordered from Toom toom on two separate occasions, and both times the food arrived quickly, and was absolutely delicious. This is some of the best Thai food I've ever had. I want to keep working my way through the menu!

I ordered the soup and an order of the fried calamari. The soup was absolutely delicious! I thought that since just every other review here complained that the calamari was horrible, and the owner's responses to reviews were positive, that the calamari would have been improved by now...NO! It is STILL the most inedible "stuff" I've ever seen. They were fried until they were completely dried out, and the calamari (IF there was any actually in there) was hard as a rock. Since the owners don't care that they are selling stuff that cannot be eaten, I can only surmise that they are continuing to sell it to carry out/delivery orders so it can't be returned and no refund has to be given. It will always be extra money for them that they steal from their customers because they know the customer will NOT be able to eat it. So, even though the soup was delicious, I'll never order from nor eat in this restaurant again. I do not patronize businesses that deliberately rip off their customers like this.

Ordered through doordash. The order arrived wrong. By the time I got hold of the restaurant they were closed. The young man who answered the phone sounded sincere but also explained that I'd have to work with doordash to make it right. I confirmed though that nothing would be corrected that night and I was S.O.L. and without my dinner. We hung up and I was obviously not happy. My phone rang about 1 minute later. The same young man explained that he told the owner what happened. I could hear the owner in the background telling him that he will cook it himself and will bring it to my house himself. 15 minutes later there is the owner with my food. He was apologetic, polite and most importantly he took care of his customer. I will recommend this place to everyone.  This level of service is a dying act. Thank you Toom Toom Thai for caring about your customers.

Toom Toom Thai is hands down, the absolute BEST Thai restaurant EVER!  Everything on their menu is so fresh and delicious--I have so many favorites, but I highly recommend their crab rangoons, sesame chicken, Thai iced coffee, and the sticky rice with fresh mango, or their homemade coconut ice cream.  Mama Toom is from Thailand, and she and her cooking is the REAL DEAL, no Americanized  Thai or Asian food served here.  The service is pretty good, and even though it's not the speediest (they run on a small staff, but the wait isn't unreasonable either), it's more than worth the wait, and Mama Toom welcomes everyone, treating all of her customers like family.  I've been going there for the past several years, and the quality of the food and service is consistently excellent--HIGHLY RECOMMEND!
I love this place, the staff, the food, they have a Taro cake dessert to die for.

WOW. Just wow. This place is insanely delicious! The menu is simple and straightforward, with all the familiar classics and a few unique options that aren't as common definitely worth trying. I ordered the panang curry noodles with chicken and was blown away by how insanely flavorful and delicious it was. It's quite thick and not watered down at all, so the flavors really pack a punch. I didn't have any previous expectations but was pleasantly surprised. I like the idea that you can build your own bowl when it comes to ordering the curry noodles, and the egg noodles were a great choice. The noodles held on to the curry really well and had a great slightly chewy texture. I enjoy spicy food, and while this dish had a fair amount of heat, it was just enough that it didn't hurt and was very tolerable. I've never eaten a whole bowl of curry before in one sitting, but I finished every last drop of this. It was that good. The service was great as well and all the staff were really friendly. I highly HIGHLY recommend this restaurant and look forward to my next visit!
